  "summary": {
    "brief": "106.    The requisite standard of proof in medical disciplinary cases was\nconsidered by Jeffries J inOngley v Medical Council of New\nZealand39where the High Court adopted the\nfollowing passage from the judgment inRe Evatt: ex parte New South Wales Bar\nAssociation40. Medical malpractice case involving paediatrics.",
